Read proteingroups/phosphosites

read_proteingroups.Rd

Read proteingroups/phosphosites

read_proteingroups(
  proteinfile,
  quantity = guess_maxquant_quantity(proteinfile),
  designfile = default_designfile(proteinfile, "maxquant", quantity),
  rm_subgroups = character(0),
  contaminants = FALSE,
  reverse = FALSE,
  fastafile = NULL,
  invert_subgroups = character(0),
  impute = stri_detect_regex(quantity, "[Ii]ntensity"),
  verbose = TRUE,
  plot = TRUE
)

read_phosphosites(
  phosphofile,
  proteinfile = paste0(dirname(phosphofile), "/proteinGroups.txt"),
  quantity = guess_maxquant_quantity(phosphofile),
  designfile = default_designfile(proteinfile, "maxquant", quantity),
  rm_subgroups = character(0),
  contaminants = FALSE,
  reverse = FALSE,
  min_localization_prob = 0.75,
  fastafile = NULL,
  invert_subgroups = character(0),
  verbose = TRUE,
  plot = TRUE
)

Arguments

proteinfile

proteinGroups.txt path
quantity

string: "Ratio normalized", "Ratio", "LFQ intensity", "Reporter intensity corrected", "Reporter intensity", "Intensity labeled", "Intensity"
designfile

path to designfile
rm_subgroups

character vector: subgroups to be removed
contaminants

return contaminants? (defaultFALSE)
reverse

return reverse peptides? (default FALSE)
fastafile

NULL or fastafile (to deconvolute proteingroups
invert_subgroups

character vector: subgroups to be inverted
impute

TRUE or FALSE (default)
verbose

TRUE (default) or FALSE
plot

TRUE or FALSE
phosphofile

phospho(STY)Sites.txt path
min_localization_prob

number (default 0.75): min site loc. prob.

Value

SummarizedExperiment

Examples

# STEM CELLS
    # NORMALIZED RATIOS
    proteinfile <- download_data('stemcells.proteinGroups.txt')
    (object <- read_proteingroups(proteinfile,
                                invert_subgroups = c('E_EM','E_BM','BM_EM')))
